Humbled and excited to finally share that my project “This Land is Your Land” has been selected to show at @rotterdamphoto festival this coming year (Feb. 2023) in the Netherlands! 

I’m in awe of all the photographers chosen for project work and single images. I am also fortunate to call one of them a friend and want to congratulate @elizalouisephoto on her selection as well !! 

More news on this in the coming weeks but enjoy some never seen images from the project. I look forward to attending and meeting the other artists.

🚨🚨NEWS🚨🚨

I wanted to post and share my first cover + feature story w/ @baltmag today! 📖

I had the honor of working on this project for the last few months with my amazing editor @amandawhiteiseli and writer @humanpoweredcity - definitely fitting and emotional for me that one of the first teams to take a chance on me also helped me reach this milestone in my career. 

The writing is incredible and deeply impactful to my understanding of Baltimore and how the city was developed. Many of you who know my artistic practice/research know these topics are crucial to me and those who have been fighting for decades to preserve their homes and Black history. 

I'll leave this quote from the cover below but PLEASE go out and grab a copy - I guarantee you will learn something new about the city and it's inhabitants.

"In the late 1960s, Baltimore began demolishing Black neighborhoods to make room for an ill-fated expressway. Will the damage to the community ever be repaired?"

Looking forward to seeing how @mayorbmscott @iamwesmoore @pete.buttigieg address the challenges facing Baltimore now that we have new leadership in the Governor's Mansion!!

grateful to everyone viewing and showing love to my shares w/ #teampixel over the last few days. recently returned from an amazing winter summit with friends, fellow creatives and colleagues over @googlepixel_us // we spent a few days skiing, snowmobiling and exploring park city.

this is my fourth trip to park city and I wanted to focus on filming video with my device a bit more. having just learned how to ski recently I knew there would be angles and shots I could only get while on the mountain. 

really been loving the different stabilization modes and cinematic features on the #pixel7pro and wanted to show some more footage from those visual diaries. thank you all for rocking with me and I look forward to sharing some more images I made on this trip soon. 

thanks to the team over @googlepixel_us @1000heads  @pendryparkcity and @hi5.agency for making this an amazing experience.

I am so fortunate and humbled to have been be accepted into @deliciastudio_ for their first ever Delicia workshop!! 

@camilafalquez and @josefinasantos are two of my favorite photographers and I’m honored to be part of this amazing cohort. 

Their guidance will definitely help me organize through some work I’ve been very eager to share. I’m already inspired by all the feedback and help I’ve received from the teaching team and from my colleagues. 

I’ll definitely be sharing more as we continue working together over the next few months but here are some small moments from our first meetings this past weekend. 

Thank you again for the opportunity @deliciastudio_ & please keep an eye out for the work coming out of this space and future opportunities. 

I’m constantly blown away!!

I'm so excited to share PCM 6 w/ you all ! It was an amazing process getting to work with one of my favorite writers @terimhenderson and the amazing team over at @plastikcombmag 

Thank you to @beebe.grafik @ths.nu.art @affinitybyserif for bringing this magazine to life and allowing me to be part of it. Supporting independent publishers, designers and artistic collaboration is what it's all about. 

As a celebration of PCM #6 being available in-stores and internationally I want to give away an 8" x 10" print to the first ten people who DM me with their copy and/or receipt. On the website add to cart and then click where it says “Cart” at the top or “View Cart” to finish your order. 

Thank you to the team @iconicmagazines for letting me take a few celebratory images. Still unreal seeing it on NYC shelves!

Congrats to all of the incredible artists featured and everyone who helped to make this possible.

I can barely put into words how grateful I am to be part of this year’s Creator Labs Photo Fund recipients. 

This Land is Your Land is a project I’ve been working on for quite some time and I’m incredibly grateful to share it with even more of you. I’ve had the support of my mentors, peers and so many others as I’ve been working through this. 

Thankful to @aperturefnd @googlepixel_us and @sn37agency for supporting me as I continue my work and expand my artistic practice. A huge congrats to all of the other selected artists as well - I’ll be spending the rest of the day exploring their work 🥲

An extra thank you to my frequent collaborators (listed below) and I’ll be sharing more of my photographic and motion work from this project over the coming weeks.

🚨🚨🚨

ARTFORUM January 2024 - Black Collagists - written and curated by @terimhenderson 

I want to start this post off by thanking the absolutely incredible Teri Henderson for including my work in this month’s @artforum - alongside amazing artists @jessicawxart @anthony.r.grant @khaleelah.harris and @severe.paper 

“Collaging is an act of reclamation and reinvention—disparate elements are decontextualized, recontextualized, and reconfigured into a congruent whole.”

Teri’s thoughtful curation and masterful writing empower me to continue working in the beautiful and expressive medium that is collage. 

I had the opportunity to share a new collage piece for a series called “Your America” that I’m working on. In summary, a further exploration into my own time in service and the plights of Black servicemembers over the last century. 

Blind patriotism, racial inequality and the effects of colonization in a nation as complex as the US are topics I plan to confront. As corrupt lawmakers and war profiteers look to rewrite history and wage endless wars abroad I hope to reflect on my own complicity within a broken system. 

-

Research/References at @nyplpicturecollection with special mention to the immeasurable portrait work of the late James Van Der Zee.

Available in-print internationally where all magazines are sold ! I picked up my copies from @printedmatterinc - thank you to that team for getting me a few ASAP.
